messages.messageBody:
On 22 Aug 02, at 11:01, Nanci Kuykendall wrote:

> >If your friend spells her daughters name "Eowyn"
> >could be from The Lord of the Rings. Middle Earth
> >history ? maybe ? Eowyn was the fearless daughter of
> >King Theoden. Yes, I read the book more than once.
> >Maybe I'm way off, but that is where I recognize the
> >name.
> >Cris
>
> Same here Chris. It's what immediately came to my
> mind. Eowyn was the one who snuck off to the final
> battle with the King's army, and who brought about the
> demise of the King Ringwraith (who could be killed by
> "no man") along with a little Hobbit assistance.
>
> Nanci K.
>

Tolkien pinched it from the Welsh.
Nowt wrong with that though.

S


"You laugh at me because I'm different. I laugh at you because you are all the same."

messages.messageBody:
>If your friend spells her daughters name "Eowyn"
>could be from The Lord of the Rings. Middle Earth
>history ? maybe ? Eowyn was the fearless daughter of
>King Theoden. Yes, I read the book more than once.
>Maybe I'm way off, but that is where I recognize the
>name.
>Cris

Same here Chris. It's what immediately came to my
mind. Eowyn was the one who snuck off to the final
battle with the King's army, and who brought about the
demise of the King Ringwraith (who could be killed by
"no man") along with a little Hobbit assistance.

Nanci K.
